 is the third business comprising the newly formed construction supply holdings stetson is a management owned construction supply distributor with nine branches and a distribution center in the midwest in november  sterling completed the simultaneous acquisitions of brock white company llc and border construction specialties llc to form construction supply holdings each an industry leader in their respective markets brock white and border have strong branch footprints in the western canada the upper midwest and the southwest the addition of stetson further expands the company’s presence in the midwest and adds technical expertise in the reinforcing steel fabrication and form rental categories construction supply holdings is a leader in the distribution of construction materials accessories and tools primarily for professional concrete and masonry contractors in the united states and canada the combined company has  branches with  employees and offers over  skus for nearly  customers “sterling has a vision to build a bestinclass distribution business and the entire stetson team is excited about being a part of that success” said marte cook president of stetson “the opportunity to join forces with brock white and border made sterling the ideal partner for the next phase of our company’s growth” “the stetson team has a fantastic reputation and we look forward to drawing on the unique strengths of the brock white border and stetson organizations to continue to build the platform” said brian henry a partner at the sterling group sterling has a long history of partnering with management to build businesses and transform segments of the building products industry including successful investments in roofing supply group and american bath group about the sterling group founded in  the sterling group is a private equity investment firm that targets controlling interests in basic manufacturing distribution and industrial services companies typical enterprise values of these companies range from  million to  million sterling has sponsored the buyout of  platform companies and numerous addon acquisitions for a total transaction value of over  billion currently sterling has over  billion of assets under management for further information please visit wwwsterlinggroupcom previous next categoriescategories select category accolades acquisition announcements closing deal deal investment news sale latest news the sterling group completes the sale of dexko global inc to kps capital partners construction supply group a portfolio company of the sterling group acquires carter waters the sterling group agrees to sell dexko global inc to kps capital partners construction supply group a portfolio company of the sterling group acquires five gerdau construction products branches home about us investment approach our team portfolio news contact us investor login nine greenway plaza suite  houston tx   p  f   copyright  sterling group lp design  development by mesh construction supply holdings a portfolio company of the sterling group acquires stetson building products inc  stockrants new york fri  jul  am    save  on hr block online    stockrantsstock market today chat forums news stock market today stock market news best stock blogs live stock chat irc chat guide stock forum trader tools guide to online trading best online brokers stock newsletters average cost calculator capital gains calculator trader video bloomberg live tv day trading radio kitco video marketwatch max keiser peter schiff the motley fool video the wall street journal trader insight your trading coach contact advertising submit a press release featured momo stocks analysts technicals economic data ma press releases you are here home  investors  mergers  acquisitions  construction supply holdings a portfolio company of the sterling group acquires stetson building products inc construction supply holdings a portfolio company of the sterling group acquires stetson building products inc j